{"key":"processedPost-16277292","value":{"id":16277292,"first":16217455,"last":16932784,"when":1337867035,"utime":"05/24/12 04:43 PM","content":"Using more gypsum won't hurt because it's mineral and fungi evolved early in our planet's history consuming mostly rock.&nbsp; However, I did a few thousand comparison tests and found that 2% by volume or up to 5% by weight(roughly the same amount since gypsum is heavier than bulk substrates) delivers the full benefit.<br />On our mushroom farm, we use one cup/250ml of gypsum for each 10 substrate bags, each containing five pounds of hydrated bulk substrate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Do you think this gypsum will work?"}}